#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn51.77-86"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn51.77-86:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 51 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 51 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.77-86:0.2"
msgid "8. Oghavagga "
msgstr "8. Floods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn51.77-86:0.3"
msgid "77–86. Oghādisutta "
msgstr "77–86. Floods, Etc. "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn51.77-86:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, uddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are five higher fetters. "

msgctxt "sn51.77-86:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn51.77-86:1.3"
msgid "Rūparāgo, arūparāgo, māno, uddhaccaṃ, avijjā—"
msgstr "Desire for rebirth in the realm of luminous form, desire for rebirth in the formless realm, conceit, restlessness, and ignorance. "

msgctxt "sn51.77-86:1.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañcuddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni. "
msgstr "These are the five higher fetters. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn51.77-86:1.5"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya cattāro iddhipādā bhāvetabbā. "
msgstr "The four bases of psychic power should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters. "

msgctxt "sn51.77-86:1.6"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "sn51.77-86:1.7"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti, "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm … "

msgctxt "sn51.77-86:1.8"
msgid "vīriyasamādhi … pe … "
msgstr "energy … "

msgctxt "sn51.77-86:1.9"
msgid "cittasamādhi … "
msgstr "mental development … "

msgctxt "sn51.77-86:1.10"
msgid "vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "inquiry, and active effort. "

msgctxt "sn51.77-86:1.11"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya ime cattāro iddhipādā bhāvetabbā”ti. "
msgstr "These four bases of psychic power should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn51.77-86:1.12"
msgid "(Yathā maggasaṃyuttaṃ tathā vitthāretabbaṃ.) "
msgstr "(To be expanded as in the Linked Discourses on the Path at SN 45.171–180.) "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.77-86:1.13"
msgid "Oghavaggo aṭṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn51.77-86:2.1"
msgid "Ogho yogo upādānaṃ, "
msgstr "Floods, bonds, grasping, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.77-86:2.2"
msgid "ganthā anusayena ca; "
msgstr "ties, and underlying tendencies, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.77-86:2.3"
msgid "Kāmaguṇā nīvaraṇā, "
msgstr "kinds of sensual stimulation, hindrances, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn51.77-86:2.4"
msgid "khandhā oruddhambhāgiyāti. "
msgstr "aggregates, and fetters high and low. "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn51.77-86:2.5"
msgid "Iddhipādasaṃyuttaṃ sattamaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on the Bases of psychic Power is the seventh section."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
